author: cmpilato
msg: On the 'mergeinfoless-revisions' branch, continue tweaking test
expectations in light of the branch's approach to merge tracking.
At this point, merge tests 66 and 68 fail.  I dunno about 66, but 68
is a real problem caused by what I think is a disparity between the
actual ranges merged and those determined to have been merged.
adding --ignore-ancestry to account for this branch's refusal to
forward-merge changes already present in natural history.
